The paper deals with worker quality control in crowdsourcing systems, which involves aspects of human-computer interaction (cs.HC), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and information retrieval (cs.IR). The techniques proposed in the paper are applicable to a wide range of crowdsourcing tasks, which could fall under the category of cybernetics (cs.CY) or social and information networks (cs.SI).
